                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=feychenie",
                        "name": "feychenie",
                        "displayName": "Frederik Eychenie",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Using customBackendNaming or customFrontendNaming with cachamanager works in 1.11.3. Update your ZF !\r\n\r\nIf someone could close this issue..\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=feychenie",
                        "name": "feychenie",
                        "displayName": "Frederik Eychenie",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-27T16:56:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-27T16:56:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45659",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=_mex_",
                        "name": "_mex_",
                        "displayName": "Markus Perl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The bug still exists in 1.11.4. \r\n\r\nThe parameters customFrontendNaming and customBackendNaming are still ignored in the _mergeOptions Method in the Zend_Cache_Manager class.\r\n\r\nTo fix this issue, i had to add the following lines in this method:\r\n{code}\r\n        if (isset($options['frontend']['customFrontendNaming'])) {\r\n            $current['frontend']['customFrontendNaming'] = $options['frontend']['customFrontendNaming'];\r\n }\r\n if (isset($options['backend']['customBackendNaming'])) {\r\n            $current['backend']['customBackendNaming'] = $options['backend']['customBackendNaming'];\r\n }\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=_mex_",
                        "name": "_mex_",
                        "displayName": "Markus Perl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-29T08:49:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-29T08:49:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46799",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=renanbr",
                        "name": "renanbr",
                        "displayName": "Renan de Lima",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "a solution for this problem (it solve my problem), it needs tests for others situations",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=renanbr",
                        "name": "renanbr",
                        "displayName": "Renan de Lima",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-26T15:03:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-26T15:03:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48453",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=abarnes",
                        "name": "abarnes",
                        "displayName": "Alex Barnes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I can confirm this bug still exists in 1.11.9 and that Markus's fix above works.\r\n\r\nTo replicate if you are using Zend Server (CE or standard) add the following to your application.ini:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.frontend.name                            = Core\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.frontend.options.lifetime                = 5\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.frontend.options.automatic_serialization = true\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.frontend.customFrontendNaming            = false\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.backend.name                             = ZendServer_ShMem\r\nresources.cachemanager.default.backend.customBackendNaming              = true\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nOn a side note if the file Zend\/Cache\/Backend\/ZendServer\/ShMem.php was renamed to Shmem.php I would guess we wouldn't need to set the customBackendNaming on Linux environments?  *Not tested*",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=abarnes",
                        "name": "abarnes",
                        "displayName": "Alex Barnes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-16T08:51:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-16T08:51:30.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
